{
  "stem": "3874.1",
  "chunk_idx": 15,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "The Austrians stayed by themselves, the Germans stayed by themselves.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But after a while, things started mixing up a little bit, because you started looking for-- in my particular case, and also the other kids-- you were looking for friends.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And you wanted kids your own age.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "You wanted-- like if I was a 10-year-old boy, I was looking for 10-year-old boys.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "A seven-year-old girl would look for seven-year-old girls.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "The older kids didn't want to talk to the younger kids or play with them.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I mean, so it was a-- so things got pretty mixed up, after a while.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "So we started making friends.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "All the kids were in the same boat-- they all had-- their parents had sent them away.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "It-- I think, in my estimation today, I think it must've been very, very difficult for the parents to send the children away at ages, you know, six, seven, eight years old, or 12 old-- whatever they were.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Because the first thing the parent had to do was to recognize that he's no longer in the best position to take care of his own child.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And that must be a very, very difficult thing to do.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I think it was very difficult on the parents, also.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, I think it was more difficult on the parents than on the children, because at least as children, we had-- when we came together and started making friends, and we were now in France, and we had a very different life.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it--- we no longer had the pressures of this anti-Semitism that we experienced, that I experienced in Austria.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When we were in Chateau Maubuisson, the transport that had come from Vienna, about 50 kids, they divided us into two segments.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
